// Filename - components/LeftCard.js

import React, { Fragment } from "react";

import {
	Button,
	Alert,
	Card,
	CardImg,
	CardBody,
	CardTitle,
	CardSubtitle,
	CardText,
} from "react-bootstrap";

const BANNER = "https://i.imgur.com/CaKdFMq.jpg";

const LeftCard = () => (
	<Fragment>
		

		<Card>
			<CardImg
				top
				width="100%"
				src={BANNER}
				alt="banner"
			/>
			<CardBody>
				<CardTitle
					className="h3 mb-2 pt-2 
					font-weight-bold text-secondary"
				>
					ReactJS Tutorials
				</CardTitle>
				<CardSubtitle
					className="text-secondary mb-3 
						font-weight-light text-uppercase"
					style={{ fontSize: "0.8rem" }}
				>
					ReactJS Tutorials, GFG
				</CardSubtitle>
				<CardText
					className="text-secondary mb-4"
					style={{ fontSize: "0.75rem" }}
				>
					ReactJS is a declarative, efficient, and
					flexible JavaScript library for building
					user interfaces.
				</CardText>
				<Button
					color="success"
					className="font-weight-bold"
				>
					Start Learning
				</Button>
			</CardBody>
		</Card>
	</Fragment>
);

export default LeftCard;
